lines.text: Repaires him with Occasion. This happy day

lines.speaker: Yorke.
lines.text: Is not it selfe, nor haue we wonne one foot,

lines.speaker: Yorke.
lines.text: If Salsbury be lost.

lines.speaker: Rich.
lines.text: My Noble Father:

lines.speaker: Rich.
lines.text: Three times to day I holpe him to his horse,

lines.speaker: Rich.
lines.text: Three times bestrid him: Thrice I led him off,

lines.speaker: Rich.
lines.text: Perswaded him from any further act:

lines.speaker: Rich.
lines.text: But still where danger was, still there I met him,

lines.speaker: Rich.
lines.text: And like rich hangings in a homely house,

lines.speaker: Rich.
lines.text: So was his Will, in his old feeble body,

lines.speaker: Rich.
lines.text: But Noble as he is, looke where he comes.

lines.speaker: Sal.
lines.text: Now by my Sword, well hast thou fought to day:

lines.speaker: Sal.
lines.text: By'th'Masse so did we all. I thanke you {% italic: Richard %}.

lines.speaker: Sal.
lines.text: God knowes how long it is I haue to liue:

lines.speaker: Sal.
lines.text: And it hath pleas'd him that three times to day

lines.speaker: Sal.
lines.text: You haue defended me from imminent death.

lines.speaker: Sal.
lines.text: Well Lords, we haue not got that which we haue,

lines.speaker: Sal.
lines.text: 'Tis not enough our foes are this time fled,

lines.speaker: Sal.
lines.text: Being opposites of such repayring Nature.

lines.speaker: Yorke.
lines.text: I know our safety is to follow them,

lines.speaker: Yorke.
lines.text: For (as I heare) the King is fled to London,

lines.speaker: Yorke.
lines.text: To call a present Court of Parliament:

lines.speaker: Yorke.
lines.text: Let vs pursue him ere the Writs go forth.

lines.speaker: Yorke.
lines.text: What sayes Lord Warwicke, shall we after them ?

lines.speaker: War.
lines.text: After them: nay before them if we can:

lines.speaker: War.
lines.text: Now by my hand (Lords) 'twas a glorious day.

lines.speaker: War.
lines.text: Saint Albons battell wonne by famous Yorke,

lines.speaker: War.
lines.text: Shall be eterniz'd in all Age to come.

lines.speaker: War.
lines.text: Sound Drumme and Trumpets, and to London all,

lines.speaker: War.
lines.text: And more such dayes as these, to vs befall.
